<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1439,1969]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1908,1933]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[690,811,1909,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Evacanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="repexus">
<emphasis box="[690,811,1909,1932]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E. repexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[873,1007,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Evacanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manaliensis">
<emphasis box="[873,1007,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">manaliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all sympatric in Manali, but can be recognised by the structure of the ventral pygofer process and by the shape of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
